user stories created by co pilot 
{

Here are the user stories for your Typing Speed Test Website project:

1. As a user, I want to start the typing test easily so that I can quickly begin testing my typing speed.
2. As a user, I want the website to be responsive so that I can use it on desktop, tablet, and mobile devices.
3. As a user, I want to select different levels of difficulty so that I can challenge myself appropriately.
4. As a user, I want to choose from a selection of text passages so that I can practice typing different types of content.
5. As a user, I want to see a paragraph of text to type so that I can measure my typing speed.
6. As a user, I want an input area to type the displayed text so that I can participate in the test.
7. As a user, I want to see my typing speed in Words Per Minute (WPM) after the test so that I can know how fast I type.
8. As a user, I want a retry option so that I can take the test again to improve my speed.
9. As a user, I want real-time feedback on my typing accuracy so that I can correct my mistakes as I type.
10. As a user, I want clear instructions for taking the test so that I understand how to participate.
11. As a user, I want to see my best results so that I can compare my performance over time.
}


Acceptance Critera for each user story {

    Here are the acceptance criteria for each user story:

As a user, I want to start the typing test easily so that I can quickly begin testing my typing speed.

Acceptance Criteria:
A "Start Test" button is present on the homepage.
Clicking the "Start Test" button begins the typing test.
As a user, I want the website to be responsive so that I can use it on desktop, tablet, and mobile devices.

Acceptance Criteria:
The website layout adjusts appropriately for different screen sizes (desktop, tablet, mobile).
All elements are accessible and usable on all devices.
As a user, I want to select different levels of difficulty so that I can challenge myself appropriately.

Acceptance Criteria:
A dropdown or selection menu is available to choose difficulty levels (e.g., easy, medium, hard).
Different text passages are provided based on the selected difficulty level.
As a user, I want to choose from a selection of text passages so that I can practice typing different types of content.

Acceptance Criteria:
A list or dropdown menu is available to select different text passages.
The selected text passage is displayed for the typing test.
As a user, I want to see a paragraph of text to type so that I can measure my typing speed.

Acceptance Criteria:
A paragraph of text is displayed on the screen for the user to type.
The text is clearly visible and easy to read.
As a user, I want an input area to type the displayed text so that I can participate in the test.

Acceptance Criteria:
An input area is provided below the displayed text.
The input area is focused and ready for typing when the test starts.
As a user, I want to see my typing speed in Words Per Minute (WPM) after the test so that I can know how fast I type.

Acceptance Criteria:
The typing speed in WPM is calculated and displayed after the user completes the test.
The result is shown in a clear and readable format.
As a user, I want a retry option so that I can take the test again to improve my speed.

Acceptance Criteria:
A "Retry" button is available after the test is completed.
Clicking the "Retry" button resets the test and allows the user to start again.
As a user, I want real-time feedback on my typing accuracy so that I can correct my mistakes as I type.

Acceptance Criteria:
Real-time feedback is provided as the user types (e.g., highlighting errors).
Correct and incorrect characters are visually distinguished.
As a user, I want clear instructions for taking the test so that I understand how to participate.

Acceptance Criteria:
Instructions are displayed on the homepage or before the test starts.
Instructions are concise and easy to understand.
As a user, I want to see my best results so that I can compare my performance over time.

Acceptance Criteria:
The best results are stored and displayed to the user.
A comparison of current and best results is shown after each test.
}